  "prompt": "When having more than one shareholder, how are profits distributed? Monthly, quaterly, after taxes once a year?",
  "response": "The distribution of profits among shareholders depends on several factors:\n\n1. Company Structure:\n- Corporation: Typically distribute dividends quarterly or annually\n- LLC: More flexible, can distribute profits as agreed in operating agreement\n- Partnership: Often distributes profits monthly or quarterly\n\n2. Common Practices:\n- Many companies distribute profits:\n  - Quarterly\n  - Annually\n  - After tax filing\n  - Based on percentage of ownership\n\n3. Factors Influencing Distribution:\n- Shareholder agreement\n- Company's financial health\n- Tax considerations\n- Reinvestment needs\n- Cash flow\n\n4. Typical Scenarios:\n- Small businesses: Often monthly or quarterly\n- Larger corporations: Usually quarterly or annually\n- Startups: May reinvest profits instead of distributing\n\n5. Legal Considerations:\n- Must follow bylaws/operating agreement\n- Comply with tax regulations\n- Maintain corporate formalities\n\n6. Recommendations:\n- Clearly define distribution method in founding documents\n- Consult accountant/lawyer\n- Consider company's growth and financial needs\n\nBest practice is to establish clear, mutually agreed-upon distribution terms in advance.",
